  • Constructor Details

    • BreakerMK4iFalconSwerveModule

      public BreakerMK4iFalconSwerveModule​(com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonFX driveMotor, com.ctre.phoenix.motorcontrol.can.WPI_TalonFX turnMotor, com.ctre.phoenix.sensors.WPI_CANCoder turnEncoder, BreakerSwerveDriveConfig config, double encoderAbsoluteAngleOffsetDegrees, boolean invertDriveOutput, boolean invertTurnOutput)
      Constructs a new Swerve Drive Specialties MK4i (inverted) swerve drive module, implements the BreakerGenericSwerveModule interface
      Parameters:
      driveMotor - - The TalonFX motor that moves the module's wheel linearly.
      turnMotor - - The TalonFX motor that actuates module's wheel angle and changes the direction it is facing.
      turnEncoder - - The CTRE CANcoder magnetic encoder that the module uses to determine wheel angle.
      config - - The BreakerSwerveDriveConfig object that holds all constants for your drivetrain
